    <a
    href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Title=Технико-тактическая%20модель%20борца%20и%20методология%20ее%20многолетней%20подготовки">Технико-тактическая
    модель борца и методология её многолетней
    подготовки</a>. - Краснодар, Краснодарск. книжн.
    изд-во., 1988. - 142 с.</font></p>
    <p align="center">&nbsp;</p>
    <p align="center"><a name="Eng"></a><font size="2"><b>DYNAMIC STUDIES OF JUDO COMPETITIONS
    PARAMETERS FOR HIGHLY-QUALIFIED JUDO WRESTLERS</b></font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2">A.Yeganov</font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2">Ural State Academy of Physical Culture<br>
    Chelyabinsk, Russia</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>INTRODUCTION</b>. The development of a model of
    tactical and technical training of an athlete continuing for years must be based, first
    andforemost, on objective regularities of the development of a bora's (judo wrestler's)
    contesting activities. The most exact information can be received by making dynamic
    studies, when a uniform group of athletes is analyzed during many years of their athletic
    improvement. There are practically no such studies in the athletic struggle.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>METHODS</b>. A group of judo wrestlers, starting from
    17-18 years of age, was observed during eight years of their athletic improvement. The
    competing activities of young boras of judo, the young men amounting to 478 wrestlers
    partici- pating in the country's youth championships of 1980-1982, were studied at the
    initial stage.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>RESULTS OF STUDIES</b>. The factor analysis - a study
    of the competing activities parameters (or factors) - has shown a sufficiently firm
    structure, excepting the period of transition of junior judo wrestlers into the adult
    group. Here the structure of activity is quite clearly distinguished from that of the
    preceding and the following years of observations. The amount of factors is increased, but
    the contribution of each of them to the generalized dispersion of the selection has been
    decreased. The content of each factor is also different. The statistical compa- rison of
    the athletic result and the attack reliability factor for the years of observing has
    revealed reliable changes (t = 2,34 - 2,76; р &lt;0,01) only between the first and the
    fourth and the third and the fourth years of observations. The differences between the
    other groups are not trustworthy or authentic. The dynamics of the attack reliability
    factor and the athletic result<i> </i>for the years of observing are shown in the Table.
    Judo wrestlers get the best results in their youth (the 1st year of observation), at their
    junior age (the 2d and 3d years of observation); as to the 4th year</font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2"><b><i>Dynamics of the attack reliability and the athletic
    result in the course of many years of training of a bora of judo (n = 38)</i></b></font></p>
    <div align="center"><center><table border="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
      <tr>
        <td valign="top" colspan="7"><p align="center"><font size="2">YEARS OF OBSERVING</font></td>
